<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Business_Rules">Business Rules</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=SMAX:2019.02/PractitionersNotes/SMAX_Config/cg_bestPractices&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Business Rules">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=SMAX:2019.02/PractitionersNotes/SMAX_Config/cg_bestPractices&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Business Rules">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Do not reference a specific record by Id when creating a business rule. Rules defined using an Id are not “portable” when you transfer the workflow from development to production as the Ids will be different between the two systems. Instead, use a field such as DisplayLabel that will be identical between systems, or use the group_id_by_upn lookup function for groups.
</p><p><br>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Offerings">Offerings</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=SMAX:2019.02/PractitionersNotes/SMAX_Config/cg_bestPractices&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=2" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Offerings">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=SMAX:2019.02/PractitionersNotes/SMAX_Config/cg_bestPractices&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Offerings">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Service offerings cannot be moved between a development and production system. While creating some offerings in development is a good practice for testing and experimentation, all offerings must eventually be created directly in production.
</p>
